                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1011">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Peirce</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Hay</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Embassy of the United States</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">St. Petersburg</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1900-08-03">
                            <hi rend="italic">August 3, 1900</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>[Mr. Peirce reports the receipt, on the 1st instant, from the Russian minister
                    for foreign affairs, of the final draft of the protocol of arbitration of Bering
                    Sea claims of citizens of the United States, with a clause inserted admitting
                    the introduction of all evidence which has already been presented, or which has
                    appeared in the correspondence between the official representatives of the two
                    high contracting powers; and that a clause has been added providing that the
                    decision of the arbitrator shall be rendered in French, that language being
                    recognized as the official language of the arbitration. With the exceptions
                    noted the draft of the protocol is identical with that inclosed with dispatch
                    No. 234, of June 6. As the Russian Government is ready to sign the protocol at
                    once, Mr. Peirce asks if he is authorized by the Department to sign.]</p>
            </div>
